**These delicious cookies are made with rolled oats, ripe bananas, and cinnamon. They are perfect for a healthy snack or dessert. The recipe is simple and easy to follow. First, mash the bananas in a bowl until they are smooth. Add the rolled oats and cinnamon to the bowl and mix well. Scoop the mixture into small balls and place them on a baking sheet. Flatten the balls slightly with a fork. Bake the cookies in a preheated oven for 12-15 minutes until they are golden brown. Serve warm and enjoy the sweet and satisfying taste of these oatmeal banana cinnamon cookies!** - Upscaled by <@1079709954350518302> (fast)
